{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016gWVVseTcfb2qypwHrvysn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The transform doesn't exist because the precondition failed. The precondition log shows that the curl commands using HTTP failed (exit code 52 means empty reply from server - because ES is using HTTPS). The precondition tried to create the transform and start it, but since HTTP failed, the transform was never created.\n\nHowever, the precondition still set up:\n1. The transform statefulset scaled to 0\n2. A configmap `transform-checkpoint` was created with `checkpoint_before=0`\n\nSince the transform was never created, I need to:\n1. Create the transform `events-by-service`\n2. Scale the `es-transform` statefulset back to 1 to restore transform capacity\n3. Wait for it to join the cluster\n4. Start the transform\n\nBut wait, the task description says \"Transform job is failed or stopped\" and \"Aggregated results are stale,\" which suggests the transform existed before. Let me look at the precondition log more carefully to understand what actually happened.\n\nThe precondition log shows the transform was never successfully created in the first place—the HTTP calls to create and start it both failed with exit code 52. Then the `es-transform` statefulset was scaled down to 0. So the scenario seems to be that I need to recreate and start the transform job `events-by-service` after restoring the dedicated transform node capacity.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":356,"cache_read_input_tokens":36246,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":356},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"afd55ec6-6f6c-43e2-bca3-7c11c76505cd","uuid":"2250cfb6-e0a0-4a38