{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Tw861dJgo9tyDxNE1bKSkL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The data nodes have:\n- Certs mounted at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs`\n- Config dir mounted\n- Various secrets\n\nThe transform statefulset is missing all of these mounts. The `es-transform-config` configmap doesn't exist and needs to be created.\n\nGiven the constraints:\n1. \"Restore transform capacity before restarting the job\"\n2. The transform node needs proper cert mounts to join the cluster\n\nMy plan:\n1. Create the `es-transform-config` configmap with proper elasticsearch.yml (transform node role, same cluster settings)\n2. Patch the statefulset to add the necessary cert volume mounts from the es-http-tls secret\n3. Scale it back to 1 replica and wait for it to join the cluster\n4. Create the `events-by-service` transform if needed and start it\n\nActually, I need to reconsider—the statefulset exists with history, meaning it was created before but scaled to 0. The missing configmap suggests it was deleted during setup, but I should verify whether the original config is still needed or if the precondition already handled part of this.\n\nLooking at the cluster setup, there are already 4 running nodes with the transform role enabled by default in Elasticsearch 7.x. Since all nodes have all roles unless explicitly restricted, I should check whether a dedicated transform node is even necessary or if the existing nodes can handle the transform jobs. So the issue is clear now - none of the nodes have the `transform` role enabled. The data nodes only have `d` (data), and the cluster nodes have `dim` (data, ingest, master), which means the transform statefulset that was scaled to zero is the only place transforms could run. I need to recreate that transform node with the proper configuration, including the transform role and TLS certificate mounts, then scale it back up. I'm realizing the core issue is that the transform configmap was deleted as part of the scenario setup, and scaling the statefulset back to 1 won't help without it. I need to recreate a minimal transform node configuration that can join the cluster using the same TLS transport settings, either by patching in cert mounts or disabling TLS in the configmap itself.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1139,"cache_read_input_tokens":43199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1139},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"afd55ec6-6f6c-43e2-bca3-7c11c76505cd","uuid":"d1cc8753-bbe9-44c0-a40d-86023ac51f7b","request_id":"req_011Cc9gnFg5jvKiAYgZLxVMb"}
