{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NPRTvWdonA8efDV6zdRPhC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The transform is running and checkpoint 1 is confirmed. The goal is met:\n\n**Summary of what was done:**\n\n1. **Diagnosed the issue**: The precondition had scaled `es-transform` statefulset to 0 replicas (simulating a \"transform capacity change\"), removing the only node with the `transform` role from the cluster. The `es-transform-config` configmap was also missing, and the transform job `events-by-service` was never successfully created (precondition used HTTP when cluster requires HTTPS).\n\n2. **Restored transform capacity**:\n   - Created the missing `es-transform-config` configmap with `node.roles: [transform]` and proper TLS settings\n   - Patched the statefulset to mount the `es-http-tls` secret for certificate access\n   - Updated the image from `7.17.9` to `8.11.1` (to match the actual cluster version)\n   - Added `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var\n   - Scaled the statefulset back to 1 replica\n\n3. **Started the transform**: Created the `events-by-service` pivot transform (source: `app-events` → dest: `app-events-rollup`) and started it via the transform API.\n\n4. **Result**: Transform is `started`, running on `es-transform-0` (the restored transform node), checkpoint 1 complete, health `green`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":434,"cache_read_input_tokens":76188,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":434},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"afd55ec6-6f6c-43e2-bca3-7c11c76505cd","uuid":"88bc9f16-be03-49f8-a5ef-1ebe4c6834f0","request_id":"req_011Cc9hZVZG9o6Re9k2gbtpz"}
